<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<chapter xml:id="ch-season3">
    <title>Season 3: Fractions </title>
    <introduction>
        <p>
           So far, we've only worked with whole numbers, which represent whole objects, like 8 apples, 5 cups, or 9 inches. 
           Fractions give us a way to work with portions of a whole, like half of an apple, one third of a cup, 
           a quarter-pounder hamburger, or an eighth of an inch. If you've ever used a measuring cup or a measuring tape, you've 
           used fractions. 
        </p>
    </introduction>

